</physdesc><abstract encodinganalog="520$a" label="Abstract:">E.R. Limbird was born in Independence, Kansas and moved at an early age to Gardner, Kansas with his family. He attended business college in Kansas City and then worked as a traveling salesman for the Northwestern Yeast Form Company. The photographs in the collection are views of the Limbard hardware and grocery stores, Limbird and Hilts family members, and scenes of Anthony, Kansas. Also, included is a series of 33 photographs of Anthony, Kansas and a number of small towns nearby in Kansas ans Oklahoma. The photographs were taken on a booster trip the E.R. Limbird and other Anthony businessmen took in about 1910. </abstract>

